        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 3:48PM CDT by NWS Aberdeen SD</headline>
        <description>At 347 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bath, or near Aberdeen, moving south at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Aberdeen, Bath, Columbia, and Tacoma Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
